<h4 id="getuser-part-2-get-facebook-user-information">getUser() Part 2: Get Facebook User Information <a class="headerlink" href="social-login#getuser-part-2-get-facebook-user-information" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h4>
<p>Now that we have a valid access token, we can make reqeusts to the Facebook API
on behalf of the user. The most important thing we need is information about the
user - like what is their email address?</p>
<p>To get that, use the <code>getResourceOwner()</code> method:</p>
