	                        <div id="dsq-comment-message-2893652422" class="dsq-comment-message">
	                            <div id="dsq-comment-text-2893652422" class="dsq-comment-text">
	                                <p>Yep, it should fly as well! Actually, if you use this authenticator <em>only</em> for Facebook - it even easier, just always return true in checkCredentials(). This method will be called <em>only</em> if getUser() returns a User object. So, your challenge here: return user only if user successfully authenticated via Facebook and you found its corresponding User object in the DB. That's it.</p>
