	                                <p>Ah, great idea! And yes, I could share some information with you ;)</p><p>First of all, yes, you could be able to write your own Social Networking Login with Guard which implemented directly into Symfony. Actually, you even could do it without Guard Component and without any third party libs (I know it, I did). But with Guard it'll be more obvious.</p><p>I also suggest you to look closer to our oauth bundle: <a href="https://disq.us/url?url=https%3A%2F%2Fgithub.com%2Fknpuniversity%2Foauth2-client-bundle%3AoQJ0hrgNHz2vRCG_tdSLFs7Z7Ek&amp;cuid=1175718" rel="nofollow noopener">https://github.com/knpuniversi...</a> . It already has Facebook and Google+ providers, and some others you want to include later and also has some example of integration with Guard, check docs here: <a href="https://disq.us/url?url=https%3A%2F%2Fgithub.com%2Fknpuniversity%2Foauth2-client-bundle%23authenticating-with-guard%3AFkM5Xk-TPfVy5ojzFtBty1_85lM&amp;cuid=1175718" rel="nofollow noopener">https://github.com/knpuniversi...</a> . This bundle helps you to do Social Networking Login quicker and in more right way.</p><p>Cheers!</p>
