	                    <div class="dsq-comment-body" id="dsq-comment-body-2704937554">
	                        <div class="dsq-comment-header">
	                            <span class="dsq-comment-date">2016-05-31</span>
	                            <span class="dsq-commenter-name">weaverryan</span>
	                        </div>

	                        <div id="dsq-comment-message-2704937554" class="dsq-comment-message">
	                            <div id="dsq-comment-text-2704937554" class="dsq-comment-text">
	                                <p>Hi Ivan!</p><p>I can't quite remember, but I remember thinking it was likely a "bug" in Symfony, possibly caused by Assetic. The problem may have been:</p><p>- router is called, cache is not warmed up yet -&gt; cache warming is started -&gt; Assetic cache warmer is called -&gt; Assetic warms up Twig cache -&gt; Twig cache needs security component -&gt; security component needs your authenticator -&gt; your authenticator needs the router -&gt; circular reference!</p><p>I believe it was a little tricky because it didn't happen all the time (depends on if your cache needs warming). And as I mentioned, if you don't use Assetic, it might not happen.</p><p>Cheers!</p>
	                            </div>
	                        </div>
	                    </div>
	                </li>
